<P>
SOUTHERN CALIFORNIA VOICES / A FORUM FOR COMMUNITY ISSUES: LETTERS TO VOICES; 
MIXED COUPLES AND THEIR CHILDREN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Thank you for your article, "Mixed Couples: What Are the Issues You Have to 
Deal With?" (Aug. 1). I also believe that much fear and hostility can be 
avoided by respect and attention given to them. 
</P>
<P>
 I am 71 and the daughter of a Jewish Polish father from Vienna and a Catholic 
Austrian mother. 
</P>
<P>
 To be of mixed race nationality or religion requires enough of sorting out and 
awareness of values at any time. But to be there at a time of "pure race 
consciousness" (during the rise of the Nazis to power) is almost too much for a 
young person. It was a no-man's land created by rejection on all sides. 
</P>
<P>
 You can understand how my heart goes out to the children of mixed races: May 
they experience acceptance as members of the human family of this world. 
</P>
<P>
 XENIA AMSCHL 
</P>
<P>
 Santa Monica 
</P>
