<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE ROUNDUP; UCI IS SEVENTH IN WATER POLO EVENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 UC Irvine earned a seventh-place finish with a 7-5 victory over Santa Barbara 
at the Newport SeaFest Southern California water polo tournament Sunday at 
Corona del Mar High. 
</P>
<P>
 Stanford, the top-ranked team in the nation, won the tournament Sunday with a 
15-11 victory over USC. 
</P>
<P>
 California beat UCLA, 9-6, for third place and Pacific beat Pepperdine, 9-3, 
in the fifth-place contest. 
</P>
<P>
 In the game with Santa Barbara, UC Irvine trailed, 5-3, entering the fourth 
quarter. Ofer Horn tied it with a two-point shot and the Anteaters took the 
lead, 6-5, on a goal from Ryan Bailey with 5 minutes 37 seconds left. 
</P>
<P>
 Peter Muller scored the final goal for Irvine (2-3), which had lost to 
Pacific, 8-4, earlier Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
 In men's soccer: 
</P>
<P>
 UC Irvine 2, Cal State San Bernardino 1 -- Michael Succi scored off an assist 
from Jon Szczuka in the second half to break a 1-1 tie for host Irvine in the 
UCI/Nike Classic. 
</P>
<P>
 In nonconference women's soccer: 
</P>
<P>
 UC Irvine 1, Pacific 0 (OT) -- Tracie Manz scored in overtime for visiting UC 
Irvine (2-1). 
</P>
