<HEADLINE>
<P>
1994 PREP PREVIEW / BOYS' CROSS-COUNTRY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Newport Harbor 
</P>
<P>
 Coach: Bim Barry (sixth year). 
</P>
<P>
 1993: Fourth at the Southern Section Division III-AA finals; fifth in the Sea 
View League. 
</P>
<P>
 Key returners: Ryan Adams, Sr.; Henry Chian, Sr.; Shahram DeZahd, Sr.; Jake 
Swanson, Sr.; Andrew Van Note, Sr.; Aaron Ward, Sr. 
</P>
<P>
 Key newcomers: Dan Overton, Jr.; John Stansbury, Sr.; Ryan White, Jr. 
</P>
<P>
 Outlook: The Sailors are hoping to put a disappointing 1993 season behind them 
with an experienced 1994 squad. Their top six runners are all seniors, led by 
DeZahd, the Sea View League's 1,600-meter champion last spring on the track. 
DeZahd was fourth at the league's cross-country finals and finished eighth at 
the Southern Section Division III-AA championships as a junior. Chian, Van Note 
and Swanson were all consistent varsity performers a year ago, and Ward and 
Adams were the Sailors' 800-meter runners in track. Adams came out of training 
camp as the Sailors' leader, while Ward turned in a 1:58.67 clocking at the 
league finals. Overton has emerged as the leading contender for the seventh 
spot. 
</P>
