</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Mater Dei 
</P>
<P>
 Coach: Rick Martinez (third year). 
</P>
<P>
 1993: Third in the South Coast League; eighth at the Orange County 
Championships. 
</P>
<P>
 Key returners: Daniel Gonzalez, Sr.; Dan Kozak, Sr.; Chris Lore, Sr.; Bobby 
Miske, So.; Brian Mitzel, Sr.; Matt Wickersham, Jr. 
</P>
<P>
 Key newcomers: Adrian Brown, So.; Evan Wride, So.; Michael Zepeda, So. 
</P>
<P>
 Outlook: In only his third year on the job, Martinez, a Mater Dei alumnus, has 
the Monarchs near the top of the county's cross-country scene. With four 
outstanding seniors leading the way, the Monarchs should be able to overcome 
any inconsistencies that popped up to bite them last season. At one time, the 
Monarchs broke into the county's top five last season. Mitzel, Kozak, Gonzalez 
and Lore head a solid squad that finished the regular season ranked ninth in 
the Times Orange County poll. Gonzalez finished 10th at year's South Coast 
League finals, where the Monarchs were a disappointing third. Miske was one of 
the county's strongest freshmen runners last fall. 
</P>
