</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Santa Ana 
</P>
<P>
 Coach: Roger Nava (second year). 
</P>
<P>
 1993: Won Orange County Championships and Sunset League titles; second at CIF 
State Division I finals. 
</P>
<P>
 Key returners: Juan Chavez, Sr.; Wenceslado Morales, Jr. 
</P>
<P>
 Key newcomers: Jesse Lopez, Jr.; Jesus Loza, So.; Julio Paz, Jr.; Raul 
Quinonez, So.; Danny Rivero, Jr.; Andres Roman, Jr.; Luis Zaragoza, Sr. 
</P>
<P>
 Outlook: Losing your top five runners is often traumatic, but the Saints 
should have a less painful rebuilding year than most. Morales and Chavez are 
the lone returners for the defending county champions. The Saints also made an 
impact on the state scene last year, finishing second. Chavez placed 26th at 
the Orange County Championships, while Morales was the 31st runner to cross the 
finish line. The latter recovered to gain a share of the Sunset League title, 
tying four other teammates. Nava's team will look for help from Lopez and 
Rivero, two players off the Saints' soccer team. Paz and Zaragoza are hopeful 
of lending some help, and newcomers Loza, Quinonez and Roman are looking to 
gain varsity positions. 
</P>
