<HEADLINE>
<P>
1994 PREP PREVIEW / BOYS' CROSS-COUNTRY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Corona del Mar 
</P>
<P>
 Coach: Bill Sumner (11th Year). 
</P>
<P>
 1993: Sea View League runners-up; sixth at the Orange County Championships. 
</P>
<P>
 Key returners: Tyler Beardslee, So; Andrew Gwin, Jr; Brian Slingsby, Sr; Kohei 
Tsujimoto, Sr. 
</P>
<P>
 Key newcomers: Kevin Clougherty, So; Brian Coombe, Fr; Richard Hossfield, So; 
Erik Logan, Jr; David Long, So; Bill Stow, So; Shawn Young, So. 
</P>
<P>
 Outlook: Sumner has big aspirations for his relatively young squad. "I 
wouldn't be surprised if this team is the second-best I've ever had here." 
Sumner said only his State championship team of 1989 had more talent. Slingsby 
had a disappointing junior season as evidenced by 11th-place finishes at the 
Orange County Championships and the Sea View League finals. Beardslee was one 
of the county's top freshmen last fall and has shown marked improvement heading 
into his second season. Known for cultivating young talent, Sumner has five 
sophomores and a talented freshman to shuffle around until he finds the perfect 
fit within his top seven spaces. 
</P>
