<P>
COLLISION OF BUS AND TRUCK IN RUSSIA KILLS 9, INJURES 7 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A bus carrying mushroom pickers collided head-on with a truck on the 
Moscow-St.Petersburg highway, killing nine people and injuring seven, the 
Itar-Tass news agency reported Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
 The accident took place Saturday in the Valdai district, about 220 miles 
northwest of Moscow, the report said. The cause of the accident was under 
investigation. 
