<P>
PEDESTRIAN INJURED IN HIT-RUN INCIDENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By J. E. MITCHELL 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Ventura police late Sunday were looking for a motorist who struck and injured 
a pedestrian outside the Greyhound bus depot at 291 E. Thompson Blvd., Ventura. 
</P>
<P>
 The 9:06 p.m. incident touched off an intense search by police. The victim, 
whose identification was not available, was transported to Ventura County 
Medical Center. 
</P>
<P>
 The victim's condition could not immediately be determined. 
</P>
<P>
 Police conducted interviews at the bus station with witnesses to the incident, 
but as of 9:45 p.m., the driver had not been located and no arrests had been 
made. J. E. MITCHELL 
