<HEADLINE>
<P>
COUNTYWIDE FOCUS: $5 DONATIONS SOUGHT FOR VENTURA CAMPUS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JOANNA M. MILLER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Supporters of a four-year public college in Ventura County are being asked to 
contribute $5 each to have their names enclosed in a time capsule to be opened 
in 20 years at the proposed Cal State University campus. 
</P>
<P>
 Funds from the "Stand Up for Education" effort will go toward paying for 
spring classes at the Cal State Northridge Ventura Campus, which has been left 
short of funds after the state budget cuts of recent years. 
</P>
<P>
 The fund-raising event will culminate Oct. 1 with participants joining hands 
to spell out CSUN-VC at the county fairgrounds for an aerial photograph. 
</P>
<P>
 "I will be disappointed if there aren't 1,000 people at the fairgrounds 
standing up for education," Ventura Campus Director Joyce M. Kennedy said. 
"People need to make a political statement on the need for increased access for 
public education in Ventura County." 
</P>
<P>
 She said the county missed its chance for a university at a bluff west of 
Ventura known as the Taylor Ranch. But a new campus is being planned west of 
Camarillo, though it is several years behind the planned Taylor Ranch campus. 
</P>
<P>
 "There is no point in people wringing their hands" over what was lost, she 
said. "The public needs to get involved." 
</P>
<P>
 The fund-raiser is one of two planned events leading to the Class Act Telethon 
in March. The Ventura Campus also plans a comedy night at Hornblowers at 
Ventura Harbor on Sept. 30 with shows at 8 and 10 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
 Headliner Bruce Baum will lead the show, with local attorneys Larry Matheney 
and Jim Spencer also taking the stage to help the higher education cause. 
</P>
<P>
 For more information or to add a name to the time capsule, call the Ventura 
Campus at 654-4575, or send payment to CSUN, Ventura Campus, 2151 Alessandro 
Drive, Suite 140, Ventura 93001. JOANNA M. MILLER 
</P>
</TEXT>
