PEOPLE: GRAZIADIO SUCCEEDS ELTINGE AT HELM OF IMPERIAL BANCORP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 George L. Graziadio has been elected chairman of Imperial Bancorp, to succeed 
George M. Eltinge, who died in August. Graziadio will also retain his 
responsibilities as president and chief executive of the Los Angeles-based 
bank, which he and Eltinge founded in 1963.Imperial Bank, which has assets of 
$2.4 billion, is the principal subsidiary of Imperial Bancorp. 
</P>
<P>
 GTE California has named Mike Crawford regional president for California, a 
new position. Before this appointment Crawford, 48, was vice president and 
general manager of GTE's West Area, which includes the Northwest, California 
and Hawaii. The Thousand Oaks-based company supplies local and long-distance 
telephone service. It is a wholly owned unit of Stamford, Conn.-based GTE Corp. 
</P>
<P>
 Harold J. Walbrink has been named to the new position of senior vice 
president, operations and technology at Birtcher Medical Systems Inc., an 
Irvine-based developer and manufacturer of surgical products and related 
accessories. He will be responsible for manufacturing, operations, regulatory 
affairs and quality assurance. He also will continue to oversee research and 
development. Before his promotion, Walbrink was vice president of research and 
design. He joined Birtcher in 1990 after being with Hughes Aircraft Co., 
General Dynamics and Coopervision Surgical. 
</P>
