<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: NEWPORT BEACH; PRIVATE SUPPER CLUB REQUEST WITHDRAWN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By HOLLY J. WAGNER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A resident who had sought permission to open a private supper club called 
Tiffany's II at the five-story Harbor Tower and Marina at 3333 W. Coast Highway 
has withdrawn plans for the club indefinitely. 
</P>
<P>
 The proposal was to go before the Planning Commission last week but was 
withdrawn without explanation by the applicant, Edward Martinez St. Clair. 
</P>
<P>
 Although there was little resident opposition to the proposal, police 
investigator David Szkaradek stated in a report to the commission that other 
nightclubs at the site have created problems for police. HOLLY J. WAGNER 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Brief 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
