<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: ORANGE COUNTY ALMANAC 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 After the Civil War, thousands of pioneers migrated West, including to what is 
now Orange County, lured by descriptions of the area's lush farmland. 
</P>
<P>
 A land rush in the 1880s led to the creation of more than a dozen "boom towns" 
-- many of which went bust with the local economy in the 1890s. 
</P>
<P>
 Places like Fairview in what is today Costa Mesa and Wintersburg near 
Huntington Beach disappeared. Others, however, survived and flourished. 
</P>
<P>
 The 10 oldest cities and the years of their incorporation: 
</P>
<P>
 City: Year 
</P>
<P>
 Anaheim: 1876 
</P>
<P>
 Santa Ana: 1886 
</P>
<P>
 Orange: 1888 
</P>
<P>
 Fullerton: 1904 
</P>
<P>
 Huntington Beach: 1909 
</P>
<P>
 Seal Beach: 1915 
</P>
<P>
 Brea: 1917 
</P>
<P>
 La Habra: 1925 
</P>
<P>
 Placentia: 1926 
</P>
<P>
 Laguna Beach: 1927 
</P>
<P>
 Source: County of Orange 
</P>
</TEXT>
