<HEADLINE>
<P>
6-YEAR-OLD HIT BY CAR IS ON LIFE-SUPPORT SYSTEM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JEANNETTE REGALADO 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 6-year-old girl remained in critical condition Sunday after she was struck 
by a car as she crossed the street, a hospital official said.  
</P>
<P>
 Authorities identified the child as Mary Beth Holliday of Granada Hills.She 
sustained severe head injuries and is on a life-support system, Los Angeles 
police said. 
</P>
<P>
 The girl was walking with her 8-year-old brother at about 9 a.m. Saturday and 
attempted to cross the street about in the 10400 block of Debra Avenue when she 
was struck by a car driven by Rozik Nazarian, 52, of Granada Hills, police 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 Her brother saw the crash from the sidewalk, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 Witnesses told police that Nazarian was driving about 45 m.p.h. and did not 
appear to see the girl dart into the street. Nazarian was not arrested, police 
said, but the investigation is continuing. JEANNETTE REGALADO 
</P>
</TEXT>
