<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: SAN JUAN CAPISTRANO; DOWNTOWN ROADWORK WILL SLOW TRAFFIC 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JEFF BEAN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Patience will be a necessary virtue of downtown motorists starting Oct. 10, 
when paving work begins on one of two main roadways. 
</P>
<P>
 Crews are scheduled to work on Camino Capistrano between Del Obispo Street and 
Ortega Highway as part of the city's preventive maintenance program.The 
$179,000 project is expected to be completed by Nov. 11. 
</P>
<P>
 According to city officials, the project will create severe traffic problems 
downtown. The roadwork will not start until 8:30 a.m. weekdays. Work will not 
be allowed on weekends. 
</P>
<P>
 Signs should soon be posted at five intersections urging motorists to take 
alternate routes on San Juan Creek Road and Stonehill Drive. 
</P>
<P>
 At least one lane in each direction on Camino Capistrano and Del Obispo Street 
will be open during construction, but some left turns along the affected 
sections may be prohibited. JEFF BEAN 
</P>
</TEXT>
