<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: SAN JUAN CAPISTRANO; MISSION PLANS NEW MEMBERSHIP PROGRAM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JEFF BEAN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Mission San Juan Capistrano plans to begin a new membership program this month 
that will offer benefits for South County residents. 
</P>
<P>
 For a basic fee of $35 for one year, members will receive free passes for 
guests, a quarterly newsletter, discounts at the mission's gift shop, access to 
special member events and more. 
</P>
<P>
 Membership proceeds will go toward preservation of the 218-year-old mission. 
</P>
<P>
 Paving stone tiles engraved with donors' names are available for $100, $200, 
$300 or $1,500. 
</P>
<P>
 The tiles will be put on pathways near the entrance of the mission, and money 
raised benefits the mission's preservation. 
</P>
<P>
 For more information, call (714) 248-2049. JEFF BEAN 
</P>
</TEXT>
