<P>
HOMES LOSE POWER WHEN CABLE FAILS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A portion of Los Alamitos and a small area of Cypress were without electric 
power for more than three hours Sunday morning when an underground cable 
failed, a utility spokesman said. 
</P>
<P>
 A total of 1,050 Southern California Edison customers, the vast majority of 
them in residences, lost power about 7:50 a.m. when a feeder cable in the Long 
Beach area failed, said Ron Whittemore, an Edison spokesman.Most of the homes 
affected are in the Lakewood, Long Beach and Hawaiian Gardens area, although 
about 100 homes in Los Alamitos and Cypress and several traffic signals in Los 
Alamitos also had their power knocked out, Whittemore said. 
</P>
<P>
 All power was restored by 11:34 a.m., Whittemore said. 
</P>
<P>
 The cause of the outage had not been determined Sunday and remained under 
investigation, Whittemore said. 
