<HEADLINE>
<P>
SOUTHLAND PREVIEW / THE BUSINESS WEEK AHEAD: ORANGE COUNTY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Unemployment Data Due: August's jobless figures for Orange County are expected 
to be released Friday by the State Employment Development Department in 
Sacramento.Accompanying the report will be a monthly tally of jobs at 
businesses within the county. The August unemployment figure is not expected to 
exceed the 6.6% rate reported for July. Local economists have said they expect 
county employers to add jobs during the second half of 1994 after several years 
of steady employment declines. 
</P>
