SOUTHLAND PREVIEW / THE BUSINESS WEEK AHEAD: SOUTHLAND 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Bracing for Hughes Layoffs: Hughes Aircraft Co. is expected to unveil today 
the details of plans to consolidate its defense-electronics lines in El 
Segundo, Fullerton, Long Beach and perhaps other sites, and employees are 
bracing for job cuts that could total 3,400. Hughes said in June that the 
streamlining would center around its radar and warfare electronics groups at 
those locations, which are saddled with excess capacity due to the slide in 
Pentagon spending. Even Hughes' 350-acre Fullerton plant, which employs 6,800, 
is considered a candidate for closure, because Hughes is using only about 
two-thirds of the available space there. 
